  </properties>
  <body>
  
    <link rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="Eoulsan updates" href="eoulsan.rss" />
  
    <section name="Download Eoulsan version @@@VERSION@@@">
      <p>
        Eoulsan is distributed in several formats for your convenience.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <!--a href="/sgdb/download.php?ref=lbdl/eoulsan-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.gz"-->
          <a href="@@@APPNAMEMIN@@@-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.gz">	
            <code>.tar.gz</code> archive
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <!--a href="/sgdb/download.php?ref=lbdl/eoulsan-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.bz2"-->
          <a href="@@@APPNAMEMIN@@@-@@@VERSION@@@.tar.bz2">
            <code>.tar.bz2</code> archive
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <!--a href="/sgdb/download.php?ref=lbdl/eoulsan-@@@VERSION@@@.zip"-->
          <a href="@@@APPNAMEMIN@@@-@@@VERSION@@@.zip">
            <code>.zip</code> archive
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Eoulsan is distributed under the
        <a href="license.html">General Public License</a>.
      </p>
      <p>A full changelog is available in the <a href="changes-report.html">release note page</a>.</p>
      <a name="requirements"/>
      <subsection name="System Requirements">
        <table>
	  <tr>
	    <th>Component</th>
	    <th>Comment</th>
	  </tr>
	      <tr>
            <td>Java Runtime Environment (J2SE)</td>
            <td>6.0 or above (5.0 may work, however Java 6.0 is fastest). We strongly recommand 
            the sun/oracle version of the jre (not JRockit). 
            You can check your installed jre version with <source>java -version</source>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Memory</td>
            <td>By default 2048 MiB are allocated to the JVM for running Eoulsan.
            You can edit this value in the <code>eoulsan.sh</code> file with the 
            <b>-Xmx</b> option of the JVM. However Eoulsan use external tools 
            like soap that also need memory, 8 GiB seem to be
            a good amount of memory to run Eoulsan.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Processor architecture</td>
            <td>Any architecture processor that can run Java and Soap. 
            Multi processors or multi cores system (SMP) are strongly recommended.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Operating System</td>
            <td>
		Eoulsan can only works on *nix system as some externals tools (genometools 
		and soap) can't run under Microsoft Windows.<!--  <b>Note for Mac OS X that soap 
		seem buggy under this operating system, so Eoulsan<u> will fail</u> if you use the Redundancy filter</b>-->
u
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>

